The paper deals with the analysis and optimization of hashing algorithms, which is a fundamental topic in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the trade-off between memory utilization and computational efficiency, which is a common theme in information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for hash lookups that involves two memory accesses, which is relevant to the field of algorithms (cs.AL) and systems and control (cs.SY).
